      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_46gc' title='Col. 46GC &mdash; HL Deb 29 June 1999 vol 603 c46GC' name='column_46gc' href='#column_46gc' rel='bookmark'>46GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0603P0-01742'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0603P0_19990629_GCR_223' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Schedule 1 [<span class="italic">Schedule to be inserted as the Third Schedule to the <a href="/acts/national-parks-and-access-to-the-countryside-act-1949">National Parks and Access to the Countryside Act 1949</a></span>]:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0603P0-01743'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0603P0_19990629_GCR_224' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="member">Lord Renton of Mount Harry</span> moved Amendment No. 32:
        <q>Page 7, line 9, after ("120") insert ("(except subsection (3)")</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0603P0-01744'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0603P0_19990629_GCR_225' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Lord said: I am not quite sure of the Minister's position in relation to the six amendments which withdraw the powers of compulsion. They are only withdrawing something that is in the Bill to which I do not imagine she objects. If she does, I will not move them. I beg to move.
      </p>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0603P0-01745'>
        <a name='S5LV0603P0_19990629_GCR_226'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-josephine-farrington' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0603P0_19990629_GCR_226' title='Link to this speech by Ms Josephine Farrington' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
